   <a href=\"https://producthunt.com/posts/straion\" target=\"_blank\">Straion</a>\n   251→                    </div>\n   252→                    <div class=\"product-name\">Enterprise-focused AI coding agent</div>\n   253→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   254→                        Solves the \"babysitting problem\" by providing organizational context and rules automatically, ensuring agents work within enterprise constraints. Founded by ex-Elastic, Dynatrace, Netlify team.\n   255→                    </div>\n   256→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   257→                        <strong>Category:</strong> code agent\n   258→                    </div>\n   259→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   260→                        <strong>Released:</strong> 2026-02-22\n   261→                    </div>\n   262→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   263→                        <strong>Source:</strong> Product Hunt\n   264→                    </div>\n   265→                    <div class=\"quote\">\n   266→                        \"Reached #2 on Product Hunt with 349 upvotes\"\n   267→                    </div>\n   268→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   269→                        <span class=\"tag\">enterprise</span>\n   270→                        <span class=\"tag\">productivity</span>\n   271→                    </div>\n   272→                </div>\n   273→\n   274→                <div class=\"item\">\n   275→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   276→                        <a href=\"https://producthunt.com/posts/base44\" target=\"_blank\">Base44 Backend Platform</a>\n   277→                    </div>\n   278→                    <div class=\"product-name\">Complete backend service platform</div>\n   279→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   280→                        Full-stack deployment platform for AI agent applications with no configuration required, optimized for Claude Code and Cursor. $80M acquired by Wix, built by 9-person team with no funding.\n   281→                    </div>\n   282→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   283→                        <strong>Category:</strong> workflow agent\n   284→                    </div>\n   285→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   286→                        <strong>Released:</strong> 2026-02-16\n   287→                    </div>\n   288→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   289→                        <strong>Source:</strong> Product Hunt\n   290→                    </div>\n   291→                    <div class=\"quote\">\n   292→                        \"Built in 180 days by solo founder • 462 upvotes\"\n   293→                    </div>\n   294→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   295→                        <span class=\"tag\">backend</span>\n   296→                        <span class=\"tag\">deployment</span>\n   297→                        <span class=\"tag\">claude-code</span>\n   298→                        <span class=\"tag\">cursor</span>\n   299→                    </div>\n   300→                </div>\n   301→            </section>\n   302→\n   303→            <!-- Whitelist Updates Column (35%) -->\n   304→            <section class=\"column\" id=\"whitelist-updates\">\n   305→                <div class=\"column-header\">Whitelist Updates (7)</div>\n   306→\n   307→                <div class=\"item\">\n   308→                    <div class=\"product-name\">Claude Code</div>\n   309→                    <div class=\"update-title\">Claude Code 2.1.0 - Major Agent Infrastructure Update</div>\n   310→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   311→                        Massive update with 1,096 code commits introducing Skills Hot Reload, enhanced hooks system, isolated sub-agent contexts, multi-language support, and /teleport for remote session sync.\n   312→                    </div>\n   313→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   314→                        <strong>Date:</strong> 2026-01-09\n   315→                    </div>\n   316→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   317→                        <strong>Type:</strong> release\n   318→                    </div>\n   319→                    <div class=\"quote\">\n   320→                        \"2.1 and pre-2.1 versions are completely different species\"\n   321→                    </div>\n   322→                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   323→                        <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code\" target=\"_blank\">View on GitHub →</a>\n   324→                    </div>\n   325→                </div>\n   326→\n   327→                <div class=\"item\">\n   328→                    <div class=\"product-name\">GitHub Copilot</div>\n   329→                    <div class=\"update-title\">GPT-5.3-Codex Model Integration</div>\n   330→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   331→                        ~25% performance improvement in agentic coding tasks with reduced latency for complex workflows. Improved stability for multi-tool-dependent workflows.\n   332→                    </div>\n   333→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   334→                        <strong>Date:</strong> 2025-02-09\n   335→                    </div>\n   336→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   337→                        <strong>Type:</strong> feature\n   338→                    </div>\n   339→                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   340→                        <a href=\"https://github.com/features/copilot\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more →</a>\n   341→                    </div>\n   342→                </div>\n   343→\n   344→                <div class=\"item\">\n   345→                    <div class=\"product-name\">GitHub Copilot</div>\n   346→                    <div class=\"update-title\">Vision Feature - Images to Code</div>\n   347→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   348→                        Upload screenshots, photos, or charts and Copilot generates corresponding interfaces, code, and alt text. Transforms visual ideas directly into programming code.\n   349→                    </div>\n   350→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   351→                        <strong>Date:</strong> 2025-02-27\n   352→                    </div>\n   353→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   354→                        <strong>Type:</strong> feature\n   355→                    </div>\n   356→                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   357→                        <a href=\"https://github.blog/news-insights/company-news/github-universe-2023-everything-announced/\" target=\"_blank\">Announcement →</a>\n   358→                    </div>\n   359→                </div>\n   360→\n   361→                <div class=\"item\">\n   362→                    <div class=\"product-name\">GitHub Copilot</div>\n   363→                    <div class=\"update-title\">Multi-Model Strategy Announcement</div>\n   364→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   365→                        GitHub announced move beyond OpenAI's GPT models to embrace multi-model strategy, integrating Anthropic's Claude 3.5 Sonnet and Google's Gemini 1.5 Pro.\n   366→                    </div>\n   367→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   368→                        <strong>Date:</strong> 2025-02-08\n   369→                    </div>\n   370→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   371→                        <strong>Type:</strong> announcement\n   372→                    </div>\n   373→                </div>\n   374→\n   375→                <div class=\"item\">\n   376→                    <div class=\"product-name\">Cursor</div>\n   377→                    <div class=\"update-title\">Version 0.46 - Agent Default Mode</div>\n   378→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   379→                        Agent became the default mode for users, UI refresh, and Web search integration. Part of aggressive development leading to version 1.0.\n   380→                    </div>\n   381→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   382→                        <strong>Date:</strong> 2025-02-01\n   383→                    </div>\n   384→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   385→                        <strong>Type:</strong> release\n   386→                    </div>\n   387→                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   388→                        <a href=\"https://cursor.sh\" target=\"_blank\">Visit site →</a>\n   389→                    </div>\n   390→                </div>\n   391→\n   392→                <div class=\"item\">\n   393→                    <div class=\"product-name\">Windsurf</div>\n   394→                    <div class=\"update-title\">Wave 4 Release</div>\n   395→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   396→                        Major update featuring Previews for real-time code modification, Tab to Import, Cascade assistant, integrated Linter, and click-to-edit functionality.\n   397→                    </div>\n   398→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   399→                        <strong>Date:</strong> 2025-03-05\n   400→                    </div>\n   401→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   402→                        <strong>Type:</strong> release\n   403→                    </div>\n   404→                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   405→                        <a href=\"https://codeium.com/windsurf\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more →</a>\n   406→                    </div>\n   407→                </div>\n   408→\n   409→                <div class=\"item\">\n   410→                    <div class=\"product-name\">Continue</div>\n   411→                    <div class=\"update-title\">IDEA Plugin Version 0.0.88</div>\n   412→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   413→                        Released IDEA plugin update supporting deployment of DeepSeek and other AI large models for coding assistance in IntelliJ IDEA environments.\n   414→                    </div>\n   415→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   416→                        <strong>Date:</strong> 2025-02-24\n   417→                    </div>\n   418→                    <div class=\"meta-line\">\n   419→                        <strong>Type:</strong> release\n   420→                    </div>\n   421→                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   422→                        <a href=\"https://continue.dev\" target=\"_blank\">Visit site →</a>\n   423→                    </div>\n   424→                </div>\n   425→            </section>\n   426→\n   427→            <!-- Technical Insights Column (25%) -->\n   428→            <section class=\"column\" id=\"technical-insights\">\n   429→                <div class=\"column-header\">Technical Insights (22)</div>\n   430→\n   431→                <div class=\"item\">\n   432→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   433→                        <a href=\"https://m.toutiao.com/a7611079469188727296/\" target=\"_blank\">AI coding trends: 75% enterprise adoption by 2026</a>\n   434→                    </div>\n   435→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   436→                        75% of enterprise teams expected to use AI IDEs for full workflows by end of 2026. Market to reach $97.9M by 2030.\n   437→                    </div>\n   438→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Industry analysts • TechMedia • 2026-02-26</div>\n   439→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   440→                        <span class=\"tag\">enterprise</span>\n   441→                        <span class=\"tag\">predictions</span>\n   442→                    </div>\n   443→                </div>\n   444→\n   445→                <div class=\"item\">\n   446→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   447→                        <a href=\"https://k.sina.cn/article/7879848900_1d5acf3c401902pnce.html\" target=\"_blank\">Claude code surpasses Codex in Google Trends</a>\n   448→                    </div>\n   449→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   450→                        February 2026 data shows Claude code searches surpassing Codex, signaling market shift toward Anthropic.\n   451→                    </div>\n   452→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Market analysis • 2026-02-24</div>\n   453→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   454→                        <span class=\"tag\">google-trends</span>\n   455→                        <span class=\"tag\">market-analysis</span>\n   456→                    </div>\n   457→                </div>\n   458→\n   459→                <div class=\"item\">\n   460→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   461→                        <a href=\"https://new.qq.com/rain/a/20260224A03C5200\" target=\"_blank\">AI reasoning models learn when to 'stop thinking'</a>\n   462→                    </div>\n   463→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   464→                        Beihang University, ByteDance, and Renmin University paper (ICML 2026) on computational efficiency in reasoning models.\n   465→                    </div>\n   466→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">ArXiv:2602.08354v1 • 2026-02-24</div>\n   467→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   468→                        <span class=\"tag\">research</span>\n   469→                        <span class=\"tag\">efficiency</span>\n   470→                    </div>\n   471→                </div>\n   472→\n   473→                <div class=\"item\">\n   474→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   475→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Ladybird adopts Rust, with help from AI</a>\n   476→                    </div>\n   477→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   478→                        Ported LibJS JavaScript engine (25K lines of Rust in two weeks) using Claude Code and Codex. Key insight: conformance testing suites make agentic engineering safer.\n   479→                    </div>\n   480→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Simon Willison • 2026-02-23</div>\n   481→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   482→                        <span class=\"tag\">rust</span>\n   483→                        <span class=\"tag\">case-study</span>\n   484→                    </div>\n   485→                </div>\n   486→\n   487→                <div class=\"item\">\n   488→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   489→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Writing code is cheap now</a>\n   490→                    </div>\n   491→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   492→                        Biggest challenge in agentic engineering: getting comfortable that writing code is now cheap. Planning and design remain crucial, but implementation cost has dropped dramatically.\n   493→                    </div>\n   494→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Simon Willison • 2026-02-23</div>\n   495→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   496→                        <span class=\"tag\">philosophy</span>\n   497→                        <span class=\"tag\">economics</span>\n   498→                    </div>\n   499→                </div>\n   500→\n   501→                <div class=\"item\">\n   502→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   503→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Red/green TDD with coding agents</a>\n   504→                    </div>\n   505→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   506→                        Key pattern: Write tests first and have agent iterate until tests pass for more reliable outcomes.\n   507→                    </div>\n   508→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Simon Willison • 2026-02-23</div>\n   509→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   510→                        <span class=\"tag\">tdd</span>\n   511→                        <span class=\"tag\">testing</span>\n   512→                    </div>\n   513→                </div>\n   514→\n   515→                <div class=\"item\">\n   516→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   517→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">The Claude C Compiler: What It Reveals</a>\n   518→                    </div>\n   519→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   520→                        Chris Lattner's review: Good software depends on judgment, communication, and clear abstraction. AI automates implementation, making design more important.\n   521→                    </div>\n   522→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Simon Willison • 2026-02-22</div>\n   523→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   524→                        <span class=\"tag\">compilers</span>\n   525→                        <span class=\"tag\">design</span>\n   526→                    </div>\n   527→                </div>\n   528→\n   529→                <div class=\"item\">\n   530→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   531→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">How I think about Codex</a>\n   532→                    </div>\n   533→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   534→                        Gabriel Chua (OpenAI): Codex = Model + Harness + Surfaces. Tool use and iterative verification are part of how the model learns, not bolted-on.\n   535→                    </div>\n   536→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Simon Willison • 2026-02-22</div>\n   537→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   538→                        <span class=\"tag\">openai</span>\n   539→                        <span class=\"tag\">architecture</span>\n   540→                    </div>\n   541→                </div>\n   542→\n   543→                <div class=\"item\">\n   544→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   545→                        <a href=\"https://developer.aliyun.com/article/1713071\" target=\"_blank\">OpenClaw on Alibaba Cloud with Qwen</a>\n   546→                    </div>\n   547→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   548→                        Alibaba Cloud released quick deployment guides optimized for OpenClaw, integrating with Qwen models for Chinese users.\n   549→                    </div>\n   550→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Alibaba Cloud • 2026-02-22</div>\n   551→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   552→                        <span class=\"tag\">deployment</span>\n   553→                        <span class=\"tag\">chinese-ai</span>\n   554→                    </div>\n   555→                </div>\n   556→\n   557→                <div class=\"item\">\n   558→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   559→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Andrej Karpathy talks about 'Claws'</a>\n   560→                    </div>\n   561→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   562→                        Views Claws as new layer on top of LLM agents. NanoClaw highlighted as interesting (~4K lines, container-based). 'Claw' becoming category name.\n   563→                    </div>\n   564→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Simon Willison • 2026-02-21</div>\n   565→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   566→                        <span class=\"tag\">definitions</span>\n   567→                        <span class=\"tag\">opinion</span>\n   568→                    </div>\n   569→                </div>\n   570→\n   571→                <div class=\"item\">\n   572→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   573→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Taalas serves Llama 3.1 8B at 17,000 tokens/sec</a>\n   574→                    </div>\n   575→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   576→                        Custom hardware using aggressive quantization (3-bit and 6-bit). Demo at chatjimmy.ai.\n   577→                    </div>\n   578→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Simon Willison • 2026-02-20</div>\n   579→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   580→                        <span class=\"tag\">hardware</span>\n   581→                        <span class=\"tag\">performance</span>\n   582→                    </div>\n   583→                </div>\n   584→\n   585→                <div class=\"item\">\n   586→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   587→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">ggml.ai joins Hugging Face</a>\n   588→                    </div>\n   589→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   590→                        Georgi Gerganov (creator of llama.cpp) joins Hugging Face. Aims for seamless integration between transformers and ggml ecosystems.\n   591→                    </div>\n   592→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Simon Willison • 2026-02-20</div>\n   593→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   594→                        <span class=\"tag\">open-source</span>\n   595→                        <span class=\"tag\">local-llms</span>\n   596→                    </div>\n   597→                </div>\n   598→\n   599→                <div class=\"item\">\n   600→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   601→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Prompt caching enables long-running agents</a>\n   602→                    </div>\n   603→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   604→                        Thariq Shihipar (Anthropic): Prompt caching makes Claude Code feasible by reusing computation and decreasing latency/cost.\n   605→                    </div>\n   606→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Simon Willison • 2026-02-20</div>\n   607→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   608→                        <span class=\"tag\">optimization</span>\n   609→                        <span class=\"tag\">infrastructure</span>\n   610→                    </div>\n   611→                </div>\n   612→\n   613→                <div class=\"item\">\n   614→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   615→                        <a href=\"https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1ooZgBTE8o\" target=\"_blank\">Lex Fridman interviews Peter Steinberger</a>\n   616→                    </div>\n   617→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   618→                        Deep interview covering OpenClaw's development, AI accessibility, and philosophy: \"You can't compete with someone who's doing it purely for fun.\"\n   619→                    </div>\n   620→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Lex Fridman Podcast • 2026-02-20</div>\n   621→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   622→                        <span class=\"tag\">interview</span>\n   623→                        <span class=\"tag\">philosophy</span>\n   624→                    </div>\n   625→                </div>\n   626→\n   627→                <div class=\"item\">\n   628→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   629→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Gemini 3.1 Pro released</a>\n   630→                    </div>\n   631→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   632→                        $2/million input, $12/million output (less than half Claude Opus 4.6). Improved SVG performance but slow response at launch due to high demand.\n   633→                    </div>\n   634→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Simon Willison • 2026-02-19</div>\n   635→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   636→                        <span class=\"tag\">release</span>\n   637→                        <span class=\"tag\">google</span>\n   638→                    </div>\n   639→                </div>\n   640→\n   641→                <div class=\"item\">\n   642→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   643→                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">SWE-bench February 2026 leaderboard</a>\n   644→                    </div>\n   645→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   646→                        Top performers: Claude 4.5 Opus (76.8%), Gemini 3 Flash (75.8%), Claude Opus 4.6 (75.6%). Several Chinese models in top 10.\n   647→                    </div>\n   648→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Simon Willison • 2026-02-19</div>\n   649→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   650→                        <span class=\"tag\">benchmarks</span>\n   651→                        <span class=\"tag\">performance</span>\n   652→                    </div>\n   653→                </div>\n   654→\n   655→                <div class=\"item\">\n   656→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   657→                        <a href=\"https://www.cnblogs.com/YahuiWang/p/19631223\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub trending: TypeScript and AI Agent dominance</a>\n   658→                    </div>\n   659→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   660→                        TypeScript biggest winner with AI Agent projects experiencing comprehensive breakout. Fundamental shift in developer workflows.\n   661→                    </div>\n   662→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">GitHub community • 2026-02-19</div>\n   663→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   664→                        <span class=\"tag\">github</span>\n   665→                        <span class=\"tag\">trends</span>\n   666→                    </div>\n   667→                </div>\n   668→\n   669→                <div class=\"item\">\n   670→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   671→                        <a href=\"https://www.jdon.com/90501-openclaw-ai-agent-revolution-2026.html\" target=\"_blank\">OpenClaw: Fastest-growing open source project</a>\n   672→                    </div>\n   673→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   674→                        175K-210K+ GitHub stars in weeks. Local-first AI agent platform running 24/7 on personal hardware with persistent memory and proactive execution.\n   675→                    </div>\n   676→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Community • 2026-02-18</div>\n   677→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   678→                        <span class=\"tag\">openclaw</span>\n   679→                        <span class=\"tag\">github</span>\n   680→                    </div>\n   681→                </div>\n   682→\n   683→                <div class=\"item\">\n   684→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   685→                        <a href=\"https://mparticle.uc.cn/article_org.html?uc_param_str=frdnsnpfvecpntnwprdssskt\" target=\"_blank\">Microsoft: AI agents achieve detective-style exploration</a>\n   686→                    </div>\n   687→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   688→                        Microsoft Research and KAIST paper (ICLR 2026) on agent learning and exploration strategies.\n   689→                    </div>\n   690→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">ArXiv:2602.23008v1 • 2026-02-18</div>\n   691→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   692→                        <span class=\"tag\">research</span>\n   693→                        <span class=\"tag\">microsoft</span>\n   694→                    </div>\n   695→                </div>\n   696→\n   697→                <div class=\"item\">\n   698→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   699→                        <a href=\"https://juejin.cn/post/7606555195754577920\" target=\"_blank\">2026 AI coding tool landscape: 85% adoption</a>\n   700→                    </div>\n   701→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   702→                        85% of developers regularly use AI coding tools. Top tools: Cursor ($20/mo), Windsurf ($15/mo), Copilot ($10/mo), Trae (free).\n   703→                    </div>\n   704→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Tech community • 2026-02-17</div>\n   705→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   706→                        <span class=\"tag\">adoption</span>\n   707→                        <span class=\"tag\">tools</span>\n   708→                    </div>\n   709→                </div>\n   710→\n   711→                <div class=\"item\">\n   712→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   713→                        <a href=\"https://www.ifanr.com/digest/1655579\" target=\"_blank\">OpenClaw founder joins OpenAI</a>\n   714→                    </div>\n   715→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   716→                        Peter Steinberger joined OpenAI Feb 16, 2026 to lead next-gen personal agent development. Project transitions to independent non-profit foundation.\n   717→                    </div>\n   718→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Multiple sources • 2026-02-16</div>\n   719→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   720→                        <span class=\"tag\">openai</span>\n   721→                        <span class=\"tag\">acquisition</span>\n   722→                    </div>\n   723→                </div>\n   724→\n   725→                <div class=\"item\">\n   726→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   727→                        <a href=\"https://m.sohu.com/a/989890296_120343587\" target=\"_blank\">MIT: Generative coding enters mature stage</a>\n   728→                    </div>\n   729→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   730→                        AI now writes 30% of Microsoft's code and 25%+ of Google's code. Tools enable users with weak programming skills to create applications.\n   731→                    </div>\n   732→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">MIT Technology Review • 2026-02-15</div>\n   733→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   734→                        <span class=\"tag\">enterprise</span>\n   735→                        <span class=\"tag\">maturity</span>\n   736→                    </div>\n   737→                </div>\n   738→\n   739→                <div class=\"item\">\n   740→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   741→                        <a href=\"https://m.toutiao.com/article/7605608399157477926/\" target=\"_blank\">Code2World: AI predicts future interface changes</a>\n   742→                    </div>\n   743→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   744→                        USTC and Oxford research enabling AI to predict and automate phone/computer operations. Anticipates interface changes and executes tasks automatically.\n   745→                    </div>\n   746→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">ArXiv:2602.09856v1 • 2026-02-15</div>\n   747→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   748→                        <span class=\"tag\">research</span>\n   749→                        <span class=\"tag\">automation</span>\n   750→                    </div>\n   751→                </div>\n   752→\n   753→                <div class=\"item\">\n   754→                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n   755→                        <a href=\"https://juejin.cn/post/7500491122679447604\" target=\"_blank\">Paper2Code: Multi-agent system for ML papers</a>\n   756→                    </div>\n   757→                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n   758→                        Open-source multi-agent LLM system converting ML research papers into executable code. Addresses reproducibility crisis (only 21% of ML papers share code).\n   759→                    </div>\n   760→                    <div class=\"insight-source\">Research community • 2026-02-14</div>\n   761→                    <div class=\"topics\">\n   762→                        <span class=\"tag\">multi-agent</span>\n   763→                        <span class=\"tag\">automation</span>\n   764→                    </div>\n   765→                </div>\n   766→            </section>\n   767→        </main>\n   768→    </div>\n   769→\n   770→    <footer class=\"footer\">\n   771→        <a href=\"#\">About AgentDaily</a>\n   772→        <a href=\"#\">Methodology</a>\n   773→        <a href=\"#\">Contribute</a>\n   774→        <a href=\"#\">RSS Feed</a>\n   775→        <a href=\"#\">Contact</a>\n   776→        <br><br>\n   777→        <p>Generated automatically from research data • Last updated: February 28, 2026</p>\n   778→    </footer>\n   779→</body>\n   780→</html>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"
