    "content": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Agentic Coding Research Report - February 21-28, 2026</title>\n    <style>\n        * {\n            margin: 0;\n            padding: 0;\n            box-sizing: border-box;\n        }\n\n        body {\n            font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\n            background-color: #f6f6ef;\n            color: #000000;\n            line-height: 1.5;\n            font-size: 13px;\n        }\n\n        .container {\n            max-width: 1400px;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n            padding: 10px;\n        }\n\n        header {\n            background-color: #ff6600;\n            padding: 8px 10px;\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\n        }\n\n        header h1 {\n            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n            font-size: 16px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            color: #000000;\n        }\n\n        header .subtitle {\n            font-size: 11px;\n            color: #000000;\n            margin-top: 3px;\n        }\n\n        .summary {\n            background-color: #ffffff;\n            border: 1px solid #d4d4d4;\n            padding: 12px;\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\n        }\n\n        .summary h2 {\n            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n            font-size: 14px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            margin-bottom: 8px;\n        }\n\n        .summary p {\n            margin-bottom: 8px;\n            color: #828282;\n        }\n\n        .summary .stats {\n            display: flex;\n            gap: 20px;\n            flex-wrap: wrap;\n            margin-top: 10px;\n        }\n\n        .summary .stat {\n            font-size: 12px;\n        }\n\n        .summary .stat strong {\n            color: #ff6600;\n        }\n\n        .three-column-layout {\n            display: grid;\n            grid-template-columns: 40% 35% 25%;\n            gap: 10px;\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\n        }\n\n        @media (max-width: 1024px) {\n            .three-column-layout {\n                grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;\n            }\n            .technical-insights {\n                grid-column: 1 / -1;\n            }\n        }\n\n        @media (max-width: 768px) {\n            .three-column-layout {\n                grid-template-columns: 1fr;\n            }\n            .technical-insights {\n                grid-column: 1;\n            }\n        }\n\n        section {\n            background-color: #ffffff;\n            border: 1px solid #d4d4d4;\n            padding: 12px;\n        }\n\n        section h2 {\n            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n            font-size: 14px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\n            padding-bottom: 8px;\n            border-bottom: 2px solid #ff6600;\n        }\n\n        .item {\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\n            padding-bottom: 12px;\n            border-bottom: 1px solid #eeeeee;\n        }\n\n        .item:last-child {\n            border-bottom: none;\n            margin-bottom: 0;\n            padding-bottom: 0;\n        }\n\n        .item-title {\n            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n            font-size: 13px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\n        }\n\n        .item-title a {\n            color: #000000;\n            text-decoration: none;\n        }\n\n        .item-title a:hover {\n            color: #ff6600;\n            text-decoration: underline;\n        }\n\n        .item-description {\n            color: #828282;\n            font-size: 12px;\n            line-height: 1.4;\n            margin-bottom: 6px;\n        }\n\n        .item-meta {\n            font-size: 11px;\n            color: #999999;\n        }\n\n        .item-meta .separator {\n            margin: 0 5px;\n        }\n\n        .tag {\n            display: inline-block;\n            background-color: #f0f0f0;\n            color: #666666;\n            padding: 2px 6px;\n            font-size: 10px;\n            border-radius: 2px;\n            margin-right: 4px;\n            margin-bottom: 4px;\n        }\n\n        .badge {\n            display: inline-block;\n            padding: 2px 6px;\n            font-size: 10px;\n            border-radius: 2px;\n            margin-right: 4px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n        }\n\n        .badge.feature {\n            background-color: #e3f2fd;\n            color: #1976d2;\n        }\n\n        .badge.release {\n            background-color: #e8f5e9;\n            color: #388e3c;\n        }\n\n        .badge.announcement {\n            background-color: #fff3e0;\n            color: #f57c00;\n        }\n\n        .community-quote {\n            background-color: #f9f9f9;\n            border-left: 3px solid #ff6600;\n            padding: 8px;\n            margin: 8px 0;\n            font-style: italic;\n            font-size: 11px;\n            color: #666666;\n        }\n\n        .insight-source {\n            color: #999999;\n            font-size: 10px;\n        }\n\n        footer {\n            text-align: center;\n            padding: 15px;\n            color: #828282;\n            font-size: 11px;\n            border-top: 1px solid #d4d4d4;\n            margin-top: 15px;\n        }\n\n        footer a {\n            color: #ff6600;\n            text-decoration: none;\n        }\n\n        footer a:hover {\n            text-decoration: underline;\n        }\n\n        .external-link {\n            color: #ff6600;\n            text-decoration: none;\n            font-size: 11px;\n        }\n\n        .external-link:hover {\n            text-decoration: underline;\n        }\n\n        @media print {\n            body {\n                background-color: #ffffff;\n            }\n            .three-column-layout {\n                display: block;\n            }\n            section {\n                page-break-inside: avoid;\n                margin-bottom: 20px;\n            }\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <header>\n            <h1>🤖 Agentic Coding Research Report</h1>\n            <div class=\"subtitle\">February 21-28, 2026 • 23 Insights • 4 New Products • 5 Major Updates</div>\n        </header>\n\n        <div class=\"summary\">\n            <h2>📊 Executive Summary</h2>\n            <p>This week witnessed unprecedented activity in agentic coding, headlined by <strong>OpenClaw founder Peter Steinberger joining OpenAI</strong> and <strong>Claude Code surpassing Codex in Google Trends</strong>. The industry is experiencing a fundamental paradigm shift with <strong>SWE-Bench success rates reaching 70%+</strong> (up from 33% in August 2024).</p>\n            <p><strong>Key Themes:</strong> Agentic Engineering Revolution, Enterprise adoption acceleration, and the emergence of \"Vibe Coding\" as a controversial development paradigm.</p>\n            <div class=\"stats\">\n                <div class=\"stat\"><strong>175,000+</strong> OpenClaw GitHub stars</div>\n                <div class=\"stat\"><strong>75%</strong> of enterprises predicted to use AI IDEs by 2026</div>\n                <div class=\"stat\"><strong>94 commits/day</strong> productivity with OpenClaw</div>\n                <div class=\"stat\"><strong>$3.1B+</strong> combined revenue (Cursor, Claude Code, Devin)</div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <main class=\"three-column-layout\">\n            <!-- Left Column: New Products -->\n            <section class=\"new-products\">\n                <h2>🆕 New Products</h2>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://trae.dev\" target=\"_blank\">Trae</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">China's first AI-native IDE by ByteDance. Features full-scenario AI-native development environment, seamless VS Code migration, full-process automated development, optimized for Chinese language context with enterprise-level flexible deployment.</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-release\">Launched</span>\n                        <span>2026-02-24</span>\n                        <span class=\"separator\">•</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">AI IDE</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">ByteDance</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"community-quote\">\"China's first AI-native IDE\" • \"Rated 9.6/10 in comprehensive reviews\"</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://producthunt.com/posts/straion\" target=\"_blank\">Straion</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Enterprise-focused AI coding agent solving the \"babysitting problem\" by providing organizational context and rules automatically, ensuring agents work within enterprise constraints. Founded by ex-Elastic, Dynatrace, Netlify team.</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-release\">#2 Product Hunt</span>\n                        <span>2026-02-22</span>\n                        <span class=\"separator\">•</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">code agent</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">enterprise</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"community-quote\">\"349 upvotes on Product Hunt\" • \"Solves the enterprise AI agent babysitting problem\"</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://producthunt.com/posts/base44\" target=\"_blank\">Base44 Backend Platform</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Complete backend service platform for AI agent applications with full-stack deployment, no configuration required, optimized for Claude Code and Cursor. Launched February 16, 2026 with 462 upvotes on Product Hunt.</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-release\">462 upvotes</span>\n                        <span>2026-02-16</span>\n                        <span class=\"separator\">•</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">workflow agent</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">backend</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"community-quote\">\"Optimized for Claude Code and Cursor\" • \"No configuration required\"</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://cline.cli\" target=\"_blank\">Cline CLI</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Command-line tool for automated coding with parallel agents support. Offers CI/CD integration, ACP support, multi-editor compatibility, and headless mode. Featured on Product Hunt February 2026 with 255 upvotes.</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-release\">255 upvotes</span>\n                        <span>2026-02-15</span>\n                        <span class=\"separator\">•</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">AI coding CLI</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">automation</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"community-quote\">\"Parallel agents support\" • \"CI/CD and headless mode\"</div>\n                </div>\n            </section>\n\n            <!-- Middle Column: Whitelist Updates -->\n            <section class=\"whitelist-updates\">\n                <h2>🔄 Whitelist Updates</h2>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code\" target=\"_blank\">Claude Code</a> • Opus 4.6</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Agent Teams feature allowing multiple Claude Code instances to coordinate on complex tasks. Beta release of 1M token context window enabling entire codebase visibility. Positioned as \"ultimate weapon\" for architecture, refactoring, and debugging.</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-feature\">Feature</span>\n                        <span>2026-02-11</span>\n                        <span class=\"separator\">•</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">agent teams</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">1M context</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"community-quote\">\"Best for complex decision-making requiring whole-system understanding\"</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://github.blog\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub Copilot</a> • Global Dev Conference</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Major updates including expanded IDE support (Neovim, JetBrains family), multi-line code completion for Java/C/C++/C#, and enhanced context awareness for inline autocomplete. Part of 20,000+ product improvements announced at February 2026 developer conference.</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-announcement\">Announcement</span>\n                        <span>2026-02-06</span>\n                        <span class=\"separator\">•</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">IDE support</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">20K+ improvements</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"community-quote\">\"Basic configuration everyone should have - best completion at $10/month\"</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://openai.com/codex\" target=\"_blank\">OpenAI Codex</a> • macOS App & GPT-5.3</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">macOS desktop application featuring GPT-5.2-Codex model with 40% faster reasoning, 400k token input support, and 50+ programming languages. Integrated MCP protocol and \"work tree\" mechanism for enhanced workflow management.</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-release\">Release</span>\n                        <span>2026-02-09</span>\n                        <span class=\"separator\">•</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">macOS</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">GPT-5.3</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"community-quote\">\"GPT-5-Codex连续干7小时'不累' - OpenAI最强编程模型\"</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs\" target=\"_blank\">Gemini</a> • 3 Pro Preview Deprecation</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Gemini 3 Pro Preview officially deprecated starting March 9, 2026. The \"-latest\" alias will automatically switch to Gemini 3.1 Pro Preview. Also announced multi-step task automation features during Samsung Galaxy S26 launch.</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-announcement\">Deprecation</span>\n                        <span>2026-02-26</span>\n                        <span class=\"separator\">•</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">API changes</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Samsung S26</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://juejin.cn/post/7605494530017280040\" target=\"_blank\">AI Coding Tools Market</a> • 2026 Comprehensive Comparison</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">February 2026 extensive tool comparisons identified Cursor, Claude Code, and Devin as \"three major engines\" generating $3.1B+ in combined revenue. Windsurf's acquisition by Cognition AI and Claude model access restrictions were key market dynamics.</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"badge badge-announcement\">Analysis</span>\n                        <span>2026-02-11</span>\n                        <span class=\"separator\">•</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">$3.1B+ revenue</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">market analysis</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"community-quote\">\"2026年AI编程工具收入突破31亿美元\" • \"Windsurf被Cognition AI收购\"</div>\n                </div>\n            </section>\n\n            <!-- Right Column: Technical Insights -->\n            <section class=\"technical-insights\">\n                <h2>💡 Technical Insights</h2>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://k.sina.cn/article_7857201856_1d45362c001902m3ue.html\" target=\"_blank\">OpenClaw founder joins OpenAI</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Peter Steinberger, creator of fastest-growing GitHub project in history (175,000+ stars), joined OpenAI to lead next-generation personal agent development. Project will transition to independent non-profit foundation.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-25 • openai, acquisition</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Agentic Engineering Patterns</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Simon Willison: \"Writing code is cheap now.\" Fundamental shift challenges decades of engineering habits. Planning and design remain crucial, but implementation cost has dropped dramatically.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-23 • patterns, TDD</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Ladybird Rust port case study</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Andreas Kling used Claude Code and Codex to port LibJS JavaScript engine (25,000 lines of Rust in two weeks). Key insight: Existing conformance testing suites (test262) make agentic engineering much safer.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-23 • rust, case study</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://finance.sina.com.cn/tech/roll/2026-02-12/doc-inhmqmpz6669028.shtml\" target=\"_blank\">GLM-5: Best open-source for Agentic Engineering</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Zhipu AI released GLM-5 achieving 77.8 on SWE-bench-Verified (open-source SOTA) and 56.2 on Terminal Bench 2.0. With 744B parameters (40B active), designed specifically for \"writing engineering, not just code.\"</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-22 • benchmarks, open-source</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.donews.com/news/detail/4/6407986.html\" target=\"_blank\">Karpathy's \"Falling Behind\" viral tweet</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Andrej Karpathy: \"Never felt so strongly behind\" in keeping up with AI tools. Tweet went viral with 10,000+ retweets. Properly chaining AI tools can make developers \"10x more powerful.\"</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-21 • karpathy, productivity</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://k.sina.cn/article/7879848900_1d5acf3c401902pnce.html\" target=\"_blank\">Claude code surpasses Codex in Google Trends</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Google Trends data from February 2026 shows Claude code-related searches surpassing Codex, signaling shift in AI programming tools market. Reflects Anthropic's growing influence.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-24 • google trends, market shift</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://m.toutiao.com/w/1857227001200651/\" target=\"_blank\">SWE-Bench: 70%+ success rate</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">AI coding agents improved from solving 33% of problems in August 2024 to over 70% by early 2026. Dramatic improvement marks tipping point in AI coding capabilities.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-21 • SWE-bench, breakthrough</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://new.qq.com/rain/a/20260224A03C5200\" target=\"_blank\">AI reasoning models learn when to \"stop thinking\"</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Beihang University, ByteDance, and Renmin University published arXiv:2602.08354v1. AI reasoning models can learn when to stop thinking. Accepted to ICML 2026.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-24 • ICML 2026, efficiency</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://wallstreetcn.com/articles/3765726\" target=\"_blank\">Meta & OpenAI competed to acquire OpenClaw</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Peter Steinberger revealed both Meta (Mark Zuckerberg personally) and OpenAI (Sam Altman) attempted to acquire OpenClaw. Steinberger rejected both offers, insisting project must remain open source.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-23 • meta, open-source</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://m.sohu.com/a/987267072_453160/?pvid=000115_3w_a\" target=\"_blank\">\"Programming as craft is dying\"</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">OpenClaw founder Peter Steinberger: \"Programming as a craft is dying, but building as a capability is exploding.\" Fundamental shift from manual coding to AI-orchestrated development.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-22 • philosophy, paradigm shift</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://developer.aliyun.com/article/1713071\" target=\"_blank\">OpenClaw + Qwen integration</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Alibaba Cloud released quick deployment guides and \"Coding Plan\" packages optimized for OpenClaw, integrating with Qwen (Tongyi Qianwen) models for Chinese users. First major cloud provider to officially support OpenClaw.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-22 • alibaba, qwen</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://qwen-ai.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Qwen 3.5 & Qwen Coder released</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Alibaba's Qwen 3.5: 397B Mixture-of-Experts model with 17B active parameters. Qwen Coder: autonomous coding agent for writing, debugging, and fixing code. Native context of 262K tokens, extensible to 1M tokens.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-21 • MoE, 397B</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://m.toutiao.com/w/1856334665745420/\" target=\"_blank\">GPT-5.3-Codex & OpenAI Frontier</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">OpenAI announced GPT-5.3-Codex, 25% faster than previous versions, setting new records on SWE-Bench Pro. Launched OpenAI Frontier AI Agent platform for enterprise deployment.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-21 • GPT-5.3, frontier</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://m.toutiao.com/w/1856334665745420/\" target=\"_blank\">Claude Opus 4.6 & Agent Teams</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Anthropic announced Claude Opus 4.6 with significantly improved programming capabilities, finding 500+ high-risk vulnerabilities in open-source libraries. Introduced \"Agent Team\" functionality for parallel task coordination.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-21 • Opus 4.6, agent teams</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://m.blog.csdn.net/riemann_/article/details/158394065\" target=\"_blank\">OpenClaw + Codex/ClaudeCode Agent Swarm</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Technical guides showing how to combine OpenClaw with Codex and ClaudeCode to create powerful agent swarms enabling single-person development teams with autonomous coding, testing, and deployment.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-26 • agent swarm, automation</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://m.toutiao.com/a7611079469188727296/\" target=\"_blank\">75% of enterprise teams to use AI IDEs by 2026</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Industry analysis predicts 75% of enterprise development teams will use AI IDEs for full \"requirement-to-deployment\" workflows by end of 2026. Global generative AI programming assistant market expected to reach $97.9 million by 2030.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-26 • enterprise, predictions</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://m.toutiao.com/article/7606994594177450511/\" target=\"_blank\">Seven mind-blowing truths about Vibe Coding</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Emerging paradigm where developers use natural language and AI assistants to build software. Discusses how this differs from traditional programming and why it's controversial among professional developers.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-24 • vibe coding, paradigm</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">The Claude C Compiler review</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Chris Lattner's review: Good software depends on judgment, communication, and clear abstraction—AI has amplified this. AI coding automates implementation, making design and stewardship more important. CCC looks like competent textbook implementation but isn't production-ready yet.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-22 • compilers, lattner</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">How I think about Codex</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Gabriel Chua (OpenAI): Codex = Model + Harness + Surfaces. Notably, Codex models are trained in the presence of the harness—tool use, execution loops, and iterative verification are part of how the model learns, not bolted-on behaviors.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-22 • codex, architecture</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://juejin.cn/post/7609660097766014986\" target=\"_blank\">OpenClaw and OpenCode combination guide</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Developer guides showing how to combine OpenClaw with OpenCode for end-to-end automation from requirements to code. Enables autonomous requirement analysis, code generation, testing, and deployment.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-22 • integration, tutorial</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Andrej Karpathy talks about \"Claws\"</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Karpathy tweeted about buying a Mac Mini to tinker with Claws. Views Claws as new layer on top of LLM agents, taking orchestration, scheduling, context, tool calls, and persistence to the next level. NanoClaw highlighted as interesting (~4,000 lines of code, container-based).</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-21 • karpathy, nanoclaw</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://m.toutiao.com/w/1857227001200651/\" target=\"_blank\">2026: From explosive growth to delivery phase</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">Industry analysts identify 2026 as pivotal transition year where AI moves from generating content to orchestrating workflows and completing actual tasks. Shift from \"explosive growth\" to \"delivery phase\" emphasizes practical implementation over hype.</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-source\">2026-02-21 • trends, 2026 outlook</div>\n                </div>\n            </section>\n        </main>\n\n        <footer>\n            <p>📅 Report generated: February 28, 2026 • 🤖 Powered by AgentDaily Research</p>\n            <p>\n                <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code\" target=\"_blank\">Claude Code</a> •\n                <a href=\"https://openai.com/codex\" target=\"_blank\">OpenAI Codex</a> •\n                <a href=\"https://github.com/features/copilot\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub Copilot</a>\n            </p>\n            <p style=\"margin-top: 10px; font-size: 10px; color: #999999;\">\n                Sources: Simon Willison's Blog, TechMedia Coverage, Industry Analysis, Academic Papers (ArXiv, ICML 2026)\n            </p>\n        </footer>\n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>",
